TITLE: Creating VoltAgent App using CLI
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `create-voltagent-app` CLI tool to initialize a new VoltAgent project. It includes commands for installing dependencies, setting up the project structure, adding API keys to the `.env` file, and starting the development server. The generated project will include necessary core packages, TypeScript configuration, basic scripts, and an initial file structure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/voltagent/voltagent/blob/main/website/static/img/llms.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Bash
CODE:
```
# Installs necessary dependencies and sets up the basic structure
npm create voltagent-app@latest my-voltagent-app
# Follow prompts for package manager selection (npm/yarn/pnpm)

cd my-voltagent-app

# Add API keys to the generated .env file
echo "OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-..." > .env # Example for OpenAI

# Start the development server
npm run dev
```

